column5: Hello Everyone,  I wanted to say hello to all on this site. I am very new here and wish all the best to all. I would say I am a pretty good fisherman, and I love to catch walleyes, pike and bass. I even find myself on some river trying to catch some trout. I have a question for all of you.  I was thinking on renting a cottage on Golden lake. This lake is located near Eganville, Pembroke area, Does anyone have any advice of this lake on how the fishing is? I will be with my young family- 4 year old son, and my wife. Can anyone help with some recommendations on rentals? Any help would be appreciated; I will soon be posting some of my pictures to show off my skill  Thanks everyone, have a cold one for me!!!!
I can't help with the cottage but WELCOME ABOARD. Dan
No help here but welcome aboard too
Welcome!!!! Gonna have to just get out there and explore a bit good luck!!
Welcome to OFC monsterman Can't help with your question but I'm sure someone will. Leechman
